<subSubSection id="C337088DF770B132B182F8B2360543F3" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F770B131B182F8B230DB44B4" blockId="5.[151,1436,1796,2039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">
<materialsCitation id="3B45515BF770B131B182F8B230E744B4" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766756364" collectingDate="1841-03-13" collectingDateMax="1844-10-22" collectingDateMin="1841-03-13" collectionCode="TYPE" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F770B131B182F8B232C24426" box="[199,251,1869,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: From Sundevall’s original description (1850: 110) it is clear that he had both male and female specimens available. According to his manuscript acquisition catalogue he had 
<specimenCount id="9D2B908FF770B131B549F88E368B44C8" box="[1036,1202,1904,1931]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
at hand. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F770B131B45DF88F331644EC" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="5" pageNumber="526" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 98)</bibRefCitation>
referred to NRM 569856 [7962] as “type”; here we treat this as a 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F770B131B55BF86B36BC44EC" box="[1054,1157,1940,1966]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of this adult male collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F770B131B07AF84733C04490" box="[319,505,1976,2002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" value="1844-10-22">
<collectingDate id="EFD7842EF770B131B07AF84733C04490" box="[319,505,1976,2002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" value="1844-10-22">22 October 1844</collectingDate>
</date>
near Potchefstroom. The 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F770B131B252F84731974490" box="[791,942,1976,2002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">paralectotype</typeStatus>
is NRM 534929 [7963], a mounted juvenile female collected 
<date id="FF937DC6F770B131B01CF823303F44B4" box="[345,518,2012,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" value="1841-03-13">
<collectingDate id="EFD7842EF770B131B01CF823303F44B4" box="[345,518,2012,2038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" value="1841-03-13">13 March 1841</collectingDate>
</date>
near uMlazi River
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B925B06F773B132B182FF68360543F3" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,321]" box="[199,1084,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">
<materialsCitation id="3B45515BF773B132B182FF68360143F3" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766756312" box="[199,1080,151,177]" collectionCode="VERIFIED" location="Potchefstroom" municipality="Mooi River" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="North West" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectionCode id="ED3CC3C3F773B132B182FF68331A43EC" box="[199,291,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">VERIFIED</collectionCode>
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F773B132B06FFF61336243EC" box="[298,347,158,174]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">TYPE</typeStatus>
LOCALITY: 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BF6C17CF773B132B096FF68306E43F3" box="[467,599,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Mooi River</collectingMunicipality>
, near 
<location id="8EF20DDDF773B132B3DCFF68310643F3" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384EA10F770B132B1D2F94430F54203:8EF20DDDF773B132B3DCFF68310643F3" box="[665,831,151,177]" municipality="Mooi River" name="Potchefstroom" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" stateProvince="North West">Potchefstroom</location>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E995E4F773B132B20FFF68360143F3" box="[842,1080,151,177]" country="Botswana" name="North West" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">North West Province</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C337088DF773B132B182FF4430F54203" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F773B132B182FF4430F54203" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">
COMMENTS: Journal entries confirm the place and date of the male 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F773B132B288FF4436054397" box="[973,1084,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">lectotype</typeStatus>
, and the details for the female are confirmed by label data. Wahlberg travelled from the Tolwane River on 
<date id="FF937DC6F773B132B566FF2036E443BB" box="[1059,1245,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" value="1844-10-08">8 October 1844</date>
to “Mooi River Flats” (= Potchefstroom) (
<figureCitation id="13164783F773B132B082FEFC3015425F" box="[455,556,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1113,1137]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1088]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[151,1436,179,1088]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 3. Wahlberg’s camps and collecting sites (red dots) in the North West Province 1842–1844." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541743/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Figure 3</figureCitation>
), arriving on 12 October and remaining there until 24 October. He collected at the mouth of the mLazi River in 
<date id="FF937DC6F773B132B373FED830F14203" box="[566,712,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" value="1841-03">March 1841</date>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
